1
00:00:33,580 --> 00:00:37,020
=Royal Upstart 2=
(Based on "Zhenguan Foolish Son-in-Law")

2
00:00:37,325 --> 00:00:39,837
=Episode 28=

3
00:00:39,885 --> 00:00:42,600
(Wei the Fool's
Modernized Marquis Mansion)

4
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:47,000
Brat,

5
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:49,280
you haven't visited the palace lately.

6
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:52,880
It seems we must get you
married as soon as possible

7
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:56,000
and find you a position
in the palace early on.

8
00:00:58,759 --> 00:00:59,519
Father-in-law,

9
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:01,120
let's not mention this today.

10
00:01:05,150 --> 00:01:06,280
Mother-in-law, you're better.

11
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,590
Mother-in-law, please come on in.

12
00:01:07,879 --> 00:01:08,679
Alright.

13
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,120
You brat.

14
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:15,479
You look really beautiful today.

15
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,039
- Congratulations, Your Majesty.
- Congratulations, Your Majesty.

16
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:20,520
Why did you bump into me?

17
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,840
Today

18
00:01:24,399 --> 00:01:25,320
is Wei Hao

19
00:01:25,679 --> 00:01:26,920
and Ning'an's

20
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,399
engagement banquet.

21
00:01:28,679 --> 00:01:29,479
Please

22
00:01:29,759 --> 00:01:31,240
drink to your heart's content.

23
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,479
- Thank you, Your Majesty.
- Thank you, Your Majesty.

24
00:01:33,479 --> 00:01:34,200
Father-in-law,

25
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,000
please go upstairs.

26
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:36,640
Wei Hao...

27
00:01:37,650 --> 00:01:38,320
Come, sit down.

28
00:01:38,399 --> 00:01:39,679
Have your parents returned?

29
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,399
Sending letters is too slow nowadays.

30
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,920
I expect they
will be back before the wedding.

31
00:01:44,799 --> 00:01:46,000
(Feel at Home)
Tell them to hurry back.

32
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:47,200
The Empress

33
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,480
and I

34
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:51,239
plan to bestow the title of
Lady of Commandery on your mother.

35
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,359
Really?

36
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,519
Thank you, Mother-in-law.

37
00:01:57,719 --> 00:02:00,159
Do you not need to thank me too?

38
00:02:00,319 --> 00:02:02,799
Father-in-law,
I've noticed you are quite petty.

39
00:02:03,519 --> 00:02:04,510
Mother-in-law, this way.

40
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,400
You brat.

41
00:02:11,519 --> 00:02:12,319
Ning'an,

42
00:02:13,359 --> 00:02:15,040
remember to come find me in a moment.

43
00:02:18,390 --> 00:02:19,439
His Majesty has arrived!

44
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,490
- Greetings, Your Majesty.
- Greetings, Your Majesty.

45
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:27,760
- Greetings, Your Highness.
- Greetings, Your Highness.

46
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,439
(I won in the end.)

47
00:02:39,719 --> 00:02:41,239
(I didn't even have to do anything.)

48
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:44,040
(My son-in-law won this round for me.)

49
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,480
Today,

50
00:02:45,519 --> 00:02:48,599
I'm very happy that you could attend
Hao and Ning'an's engagement banquet.

51
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,079
I am very pleased.

52
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,360
Please be seated.

53
00:02:52,390 --> 00:02:53,960
- Thank you, Your Majesty.
- Thank you, Your Majesty.

54
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:55,840
Wei Hao,

55
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,199
come here.

56
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,400
Sit over here.

57
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,319
Father is calling you.

58
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,080
I already said
I'm going to the ladies' side.

59
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,159
Don't be foolish now.

60
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,319
Ning...

61
00:03:09,159 --> 00:03:10,120
Father-in-law.

62
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:13,240
I'll go greet the guests outside first.

63
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:16,080
The clan leaders
and officials sent many gifts

64
00:03:16,439 --> 00:03:17,840
to celebrate my engagement.

65
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,880
I'll go check if my aunt is finished.

66
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,759
Thank

67
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,120
you.

68
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,800
Please look after me in the future.

69
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,400
We'll look after each other.

70
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:35,520
Everyone,

71
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,520
eat and drink well.

72
00:03:37,919 --> 00:03:38,719
Wei Hao,

73
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,439
come!

74
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,319
Wei Hao, come here.

75
00:03:44,319 --> 00:03:45,560
Have a drink.

76
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,080
Look at you,

77
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:48,439
you're such a big fellow.

78
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:50,560
I can't drink, I really can't.

79
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:51,400
Well...

80
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,800
Don't you dare

81
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,680
use not having your capping
ceremony as an excuse with me.

82
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,800
Mister Cheng,

83
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,840
don't set me up.

84
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:00,479
If...

85
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,039
If my father-in-law
finds out I'm drinking

86
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:04,879
without even offering him a toast first,
how will I live my life from now on?

87
00:04:04,919 --> 00:04:05,719
Look at this.

88
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,840
Besides,

89
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:12,400
once I have my capping ceremony
and come of age, I'll drink with you.

90
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,100
You aren't leaving
until you admit defeat.

91
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,280
Good lad.

92
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,479
You've got some nerve.

93
00:04:16,479 --> 00:04:17,680
Cheng, did you see that?

94
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,800
The one to challenge
your tolerance is here.

95
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,520
Good.

96
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:21,240
Wei Hao,

97
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,479
just for that courage of yours,

98
00:04:22,479 --> 00:04:24,280
I respect you as a real man.

99
00:04:24,879 --> 00:04:25,639
All right, then.

100
00:04:25,639 --> 00:04:26,879
I'll be waiting for you.

101
00:04:27,599 --> 00:04:30,120
I'll be waiting for
the day of your ceremony.

102
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,159
It's a deal.

103
00:04:31,159 --> 00:04:33,520
Come, I'll use water instead of liquor
to toast you all, sirs.

104
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,080
Good.

105
00:04:35,599 --> 00:04:36,520
That's very thoughtful.

106
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:37,800
Come.

107
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,280
Eat and drink your fill.

108
00:04:45,599 --> 00:04:47,159
Pour it...

109
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:49,200
(I won't even host a banquet
when I come of age.)

110
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,759
(Who's going to drink with you, then?)

111
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,599
- To Your Majesty.
- To Your Majesty.

112
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,000
- To Your Highness.
- To Your Highness.

113
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:01,000
I heard

114
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,839
that you all had a very pleasant talk

115
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,360
with Wei the Fool that day.

116
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,519
Your Majesty,

117
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:10,439
we were short-sighted.

118
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,959
We held Marquis Wei in contempt

119
00:05:13,959 --> 00:05:15,160
and neglected him greatly.

120
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,480
Our visit today

121
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:19,279
is firstly to apologize to Your Majesty,

122
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:21,959
and second,
to express our sincere regret

123
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,040
to Marquis Wei

124
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:25,560
in Your Majesty's presence.

125
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,199
We ask Your Majesty

126
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,879
to be our witness.

127
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:33,879
Regarding the marriage
between Wei Hao and Ning'an...

128
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,519
Marquis Wei is a man of great talent

129
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:39,240
who possesses a heart
of loyalty and patriotism.

130
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:42,199
He and the Eldest Princess
are a match made in heaven.

131
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:43,959
From now on, all the great clans

132
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,120
will show Marquis Wei

133
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,399
and the Imperial Court
sincere respect and obedience,

134
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:49,319
without any hesitation whatsoever.

135
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,759
We show our sincere
respect and obedience.

136
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,519
(What did Wei Hao show them)

137
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,920
(to scare these overbearing fogies)

138
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,000
(into this state?)

139
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,480
Clan Leader Cui, that's too much.

140
00:06:03,839 --> 00:06:06,920
Regarding the marriage
of Wei Hao and Ning'an,

141
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,199
that you are all so reasonable

142
00:06:09,199 --> 00:06:11,279
makes me very gratified.

143
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,199
They

144
00:06:15,639 --> 00:06:16,439
say

145
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,660
that the great clans are ganging up

146
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,480
to deal with the Imperial Family.

147
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,160
Now,

148
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,199
seeing the attitude of you clan leaders,

149
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,560
I

150
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:37,360
won't believe those rumors anymore.

151
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,279
The Imperial Family

152
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:43,000
used to be a great clan as well.

153
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,839
We are all in this together.

154
00:06:44,839 --> 00:06:47,240
How could we go against each other?

155
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,959
We obey Your Majesty's will.

156
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,959
- We all obey Your Majesty's will.
- We all obey Your Majesty's will.

157
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,680
What are you talking about?

158
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,959
About the Marquis Mansion you designed.

159
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,680
Didn't you say it was already finished?

160
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,480
It is.

161
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,600
And I guarantee you'll love it.

162
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:10,399
This house is unique.

163
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:14,040
Father, Mother,

164
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:14,839
look!

165
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:16,839
It's so beautiful here.

166
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:18,680
Gaoming, hurry up.

167
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,959
Stop dawdling.

168
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:21,160
Over here.

169
00:07:21,639 --> 00:07:22,680
Father-in-law,

170
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:23,720
Mother-in-law,

171
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:24,839
Brother-in-law,

172
00:07:25,639 --> 00:07:26,160
Aunt,

173
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,879
come.

174
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,439
Fool,

175
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:33,759
is this all your residence?

176
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:35,160
It's so beautiful.

177
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,839
It's our residence.

178
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:37,959
Wei the Fool,

179
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,240
what did you build here?

180
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,399
The ground is so hard,

181
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,720
and yet so smooth.

182
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,670
You wouldn't
understand even if I told you.

183
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,590
Father-in-law, Mother-in-law,
please come inside.

184
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,519
- Good.
- Good.

185
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,120
Let's go, Gaoming.

186
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,279
Let's have a look inside.

187
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,040
Hao,

188
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,759
no wonder you never let me visit.

189
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,590
There'd be no
surprise if you came early.

190
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:56,439
Let's go.

191
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,439
What

192
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,920
design is this?

193
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,279
And...

194
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:11,079
This...

195
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:13,480
What is this transparent stuff?

196
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:14,959
It's glass.

197
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,600
Gaoming, look at that.

198
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,519
It's glaze?

199
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,160
It's just like

200
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,199
that one.

201
00:08:24,319 --> 00:08:25,040
But

202
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:27,600
this is so clear.

203
00:08:28,079 --> 00:08:29,680
And it's such a large piece.

204
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:31,040
It's beautiful.

205
00:08:32,079 --> 00:08:33,360
The sunlight is great, too.

206
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:38,240
If

207
00:08:38,439 --> 00:08:41,519
Ganlu Palace were
fitted with glaze like this,

208
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:44,040
it wouldn't be so tiring for me

209
00:08:44,319 --> 00:08:45,920
to read during the day.

210
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,720
Such a unique building.

211
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,040
It's stunning.

212
00:08:51,519 --> 00:08:52,319
Mother-in-law,

213
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:53,920
you can't see much from out here.

214
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:54,519
Come.

215
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,759
I'll show you the inside.

216
00:08:56,079 --> 00:08:56,759
Alright.

217
00:08:56,759 --> 00:08:57,480
Let's go.

218
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,399
This two-story building

219
00:09:15,399 --> 00:09:17,080
is constructed of blackish bricks.

220
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,320
It's not just made of wood.

221
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:22,200
What are blackish bricks?

222
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,200
How are they made?

223
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,840
And what is this?

224
00:09:25,159 --> 00:09:26,600
It's so neat and clean.

225
00:09:27,879 --> 00:09:28,559
This

226
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,799
looks just like porcelain.

227
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,000
It's a floor tile.

228
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:34,000
You're making such a fuss.

229
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:35,759
Mother,

230
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,879
these floors used to be
made of wooden planks.

231
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,919
Not only did they creak when stepped on,

232
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,720
but every year during the rainy season,

233
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:44,080
we also had to spend a fortune

234
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,720
on repairs due to mold.

235
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,720
Now, not only are these tiles
perfectly level,

236
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,120
but they also look very sturdy.

237
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:51,960
It's wonderful.

238
00:09:52,919 --> 00:09:53,799
Wei Hao,

239
00:09:54,519 --> 00:09:57,120
I want to renovate the palace next year.

240
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:57,960
So,

241
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,120
you

242
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,360
will handle it.

243
00:10:02,159 --> 00:10:03,360
Actually, I don't know how.

244
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,000
Fine.

245
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:06,720
I'll do it.

246
00:10:08,519 --> 00:10:09,080
Girl,

247
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,200
come here.

248
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:15,879
This

249
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,919
was prepared for you.

250
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,879
This is...

251
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,759
A dressing table.

252
00:10:22,759 --> 00:10:24,679
It's certainly more
useful than the old one.

253
00:10:24,879 --> 00:10:27,159
And all these compartments
can hold so many things.

254
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,320
Even a vanity case!

255
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,120
But

256
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,519
what is hidden under this red cloth?

257
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:33,519
Sit tight.

258
00:10:34,279 --> 00:10:35,720
Don't blink.

259
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,799
This is

260
00:10:57,799 --> 00:10:58,720
a mirror?

261
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:11,039
In this world,

262
00:11:11,039 --> 00:11:13,159
how can there be such a clear mirror?

263
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:18,890
It's surely clearer
than a bronze mirror, right?

264
00:11:19,039 --> 00:11:19,840
Yes,

265
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:20,840
it's far too clear.

266
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,039
Wei the Fool,

267
00:11:22,039 --> 00:11:23,080
how did you do this?

268
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,200
A piece of cake.

269
00:11:25,879 --> 00:11:27,000
Aunt, Mother-in-law,

270
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,679
I'm making your dressing tables as well.

271
00:11:29,679 --> 00:11:31,110
I'll give you small mirrors first.

272
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:33,480
That way, when you travel,
it'll be more convenient.

273
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:35,120
You can check your hair and such

274
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:35,840
to keep it tidy.

275
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,200
Good boy.

276
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,399
I love it.

277
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:48,039
If these are sold in the capital,

278
00:11:48,039 --> 00:11:49,919
the ladies there
will surely go crazy for them.

279
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,679
Wei the Fool,

280
00:11:52,919 --> 00:11:54,919
I also need this in the Ganlu Palace.

281
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,320
Father, you want one too?

282
00:11:59,399 --> 00:11:59,919
What?

283
00:12:00,159 --> 00:12:02,519
So, don't I need to get dressed?

284
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,440
Brother-in-law,

285
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,039
I...

286
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:06,840
I understand.

287
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,159
The Eastern Palace needs mirrors too, right?

288
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:09,799
Great.

289
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,159
Not bad, Brother-in-law.

290
00:12:11,759 --> 00:12:12,320
Oh, right.

291
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,039
I also want

292
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,080
this tiled floor.

293
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:15,840
Yes.

294
00:12:15,919 --> 00:12:16,919
I like it too.

295
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,159
Give me a 20-percent discount.

296
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,200
These were all prepared for my wife.

297
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:20,919
You guys...

298
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:22,759
Fine.

299
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:23,840
Please wait.

300
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,320
Stop being so vain.

301
00:12:32,399 --> 00:12:34,710
You're so beautiful,
so you don't need to look so closely.

302
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,200
What a sweet-talker.

303
00:12:36,919 --> 00:12:37,720
Do you like it?

304
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:39,840
Yes.

305
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,559
Not only do I like this mirror,

306
00:12:41,559 --> 00:12:42,720
but I also like it here.

307
00:12:44,039 --> 00:12:44,679
Great.

308
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,600
Then, we'll get married right here.

309
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,159
Your Majesty, the lords and the heads
of the great clans,

310
00:12:53,159 --> 00:12:55,380
who attended the banquet,
are heading over after finishing.

311
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:57,120
They're asking if they
could also have a tour.

312
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:57,840
No.

313
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,120
Tell them to wait.

314
00:12:59,159 --> 00:13:00,600
I haven't finished seeing it myself.

315
00:13:00,799 --> 00:13:01,600
Yes, Your Majesty.

316
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,240
How about this?

317
00:13:02,310 --> 00:13:04,320
Take them to
the other buildings for a tour first

318
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,540
while they wait for
my father-in-law's audience.

319
00:13:05,559 --> 00:13:06,120
Wei the Fool,

320
00:13:06,559 --> 00:13:08,039
how many more buildings do you have?

321
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,240
Father-in-law,

322
00:13:09,799 --> 00:13:12,279
this Marquis Mansion of mine
covers over 1,500 mu.

323
00:13:12,679 --> 00:13:13,759
When we get married,

324
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,790
just give me a few more
personal maids as a dowry.

325
00:13:17,559 --> 00:13:19,320
Why did you build so many houses?

326
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,990
Are you planning to
take many concubines?

327
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:24,360
Dear, you know

328
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,600
my family's situation is unique.

329
00:13:25,610 --> 00:13:28,000
Down to my generation,
it's been five generations of only sons.

330
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,759
So my father wants me to have many sons.

331
00:13:29,759 --> 00:13:31,639
Wouldn't I need to take more concubines?

332
00:13:31,639 --> 00:13:32,840
What did you say?

333
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,120
Wei the Fool,

334
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,799
do you have a death wish?

335
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:36,960
If you dare talk nonsense again,

336
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,360
I'll have someone tear down
your houses in a bit.

337
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:38,879
Believe me?

338
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:39,890
I'm not talking nonsense.

339
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:41,000
Everything I said is true.

340
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,720
How about

341
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,919
you just give me
a few more personal maids,

342
00:13:43,919 --> 00:13:45,399
and I'll take fewer concubines.

343
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:46,639
My father said

344
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,759
he wants me to have
enough sons for a polo team.

345
00:13:48,759 --> 00:13:50,240
How many women would that take?

346
00:13:50,759 --> 00:13:52,399
My father had five wives

347
00:13:52,399 --> 00:13:53,799
but only had one son, who is me.

348
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,200
I heard my grandfather had
seven or eight wives

349
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,000
just to have one son,
who is my father.

350
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,000
This task is too daunting.

351
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,200
It's a headache.

352
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:03,080
I don't even know how many
concubines would be enough.

353
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:03,440
Get

354
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:06,000
lost, you fool!

355
00:14:06,159 --> 00:14:07,120
Concubines?

356
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:07,720
Get him!

357
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:08,720
Father-in-law, I was joking.

358
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,919
You actually want more wives? You...

359
00:14:11,039 --> 00:14:12,399
Not the face.

360
00:14:12,399 --> 00:14:13,200
Hit his backside.

361
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,159
Give him a real beating!

362
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,559
How dare you bully my sister?

363
00:14:15,559 --> 00:14:16,519
Hit him.

364
00:14:16,519 --> 00:14:17,919
Don't hit my face.

365
00:14:18,039 --> 00:14:19,159
What a real fool.

366
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:20,080
He dares to say anything.

367
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:21,120
Shut his mouth!

368
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:21,799
Father-in-law, that's not fair.

369
00:14:21,799 --> 00:14:22,500
Yes, Your Majesty.

370
00:14:26,412 --> 00:14:29,242
♪Everyone says I'm a big silly fool♪

371
00:14:29,862 --> 00:14:33,262
♪When things happen,
I only know how to count on my fingers♪

372
00:14:34,032 --> 00:14:36,982
♪They shake their heads
and say I'm pitiful♪

373
00:14:37,322 --> 00:14:40,022
♪Sigh and walk away♪

374
00:14:41,622 --> 00:14:45,092
♪Little do they know,
I am sharp and bright♪

375
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:47,322
♪With a heart like a mirror,
I understand the world's♪

376
00:14:47,322 --> 00:14:49,432
♪Colors and darkness♪
(To be continued)

377
00:14:49,432 --> 00:14:51,452
♪But I keep my edge hidden♪

378
00:14:51,452 --> 00:14:55,812
♪The day I become famous
is just around the corner♪

379
00:14:57,252 --> 00:15:00,982
♪In the hotpot restaurant,
skewers boil in the broth♪

380
00:15:01,252 --> 00:15:04,852
♪People come and go,
with few worries or troubles♪

381
00:15:05,012 --> 00:15:07,092
♪The clacking of the abacus rings out♪

382
00:15:07,092 --> 00:15:11,882
♪See me differently.
Who dares to challenge me?♪

383
00:15:12,102 --> 00:15:13,722
♪The world mistakes me♪

384
00:15:13,722 --> 00:15:16,062
♪For an ignorant and stubborn fool♪

385
00:15:16,132 --> 00:15:17,322
♪As the storm approaches♪

386
00:15:17,322 --> 00:15:19,722
♪I just shrug and watch with a smile♪

387
00:15:19,932 --> 00:15:21,652
♪This foolish image is convenient♪

388
00:15:21,652 --> 00:15:23,632
♪I use it as a protective shield♪

389
00:15:23,802 --> 00:15:25,552
♪Navigating with ease, I attract♪

390
00:15:25,552 --> 00:15:27,652
♪A lucky star to accompany me♪

391
00:15:27,652 --> 00:15:29,122
♪In a peaceful golden age♪

392
00:15:29,122 --> 00:15:31,352
♪I hold my lady's hand
to watch the world♪

393
00:15:31,572 --> 00:15:32,772
♪Pouring youth and fireworks♪

394
00:15:32,772 --> 00:15:35,292
♪Into a precious glazed cup♪

395
00:15:35,422 --> 00:15:37,132
♪Having experienced life's changes♪

396
00:15:37,132 --> 00:15:38,412
♪And tasted its highs and lows♪

397
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:39,982
♪My wish has finally come true♪

398
00:15:39,982 --> 00:15:41,022
♪To stay by your side♪

399
00:15:41,022 --> 00:15:42,942
♪In this fleeting world♪

400
00:15:43,112 --> 00:15:46,362
♪We are free and happy♪

401
00:15:48,275 --> 00:15:51,813
♪The world will finally
see my hidden light♪

402
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,087
♪Amidst the tea leaves' drift,
I watch life's♪

403
00:15:54,152 --> 00:15:56,200
♪Joys and sorrows♪

404
00:15:56,362 --> 00:15:58,382
♪I keep my edge hidden♪

405
00:15:58,382 --> 00:16:02,742
♪The day I become famous
is just around the corner♪

406
00:16:04,182 --> 00:16:07,912
♪In the hotpot restaurant,
skewers boil in the broth♪

407
00:16:08,182 --> 00:16:11,782
♪People come and go,
with few worries or troubles♪

408
00:16:11,942 --> 00:16:14,022
♪The clacking of the abacus rings out♪

409
00:16:14,022 --> 00:16:18,812
♪See me differently.
Who dares to challenge me?♪

410
00:16:18,887 --> 00:16:20,667
♪From a nobody♪

411
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:22,567
♪To someone now famous♪

412
00:16:22,677 --> 00:16:24,107
♪Ordinary people laugh at me♪

413
00:16:24,107 --> 00:16:26,617
♪But I laugh at how
they cannot see through it all♪

414
00:16:26,717 --> 00:16:28,297
♪Let others plot and scheme♪

415
00:16:28,297 --> 00:16:30,367
♪I will keep my heart unchanged♪

416
00:16:30,577 --> 00:16:32,257
♪In this vast world♪

417
00:16:32,257 --> 00:16:34,257
♪I find my own leisurely freedom♪

418
00:16:34,407 --> 00:16:36,617
♪The world is bustling,
and things constantly change♪

419
00:16:36,617 --> 00:16:38,207
♪Everything ends eventually♪

420
00:16:38,297 --> 00:16:39,797
♪All that remains before my eyes♪

421
00:16:39,797 --> 00:16:42,197
♪Is this street wandering,
still tinged with pity♪

422
00:16:42,197 --> 00:16:43,907
♪No matter how time flies♪

423
00:16:43,907 --> 00:16:45,067
♪Even if the falling snow♪

424
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,697
♪Dyes the hair at our temples white♪

425
00:16:46,697 --> 00:16:47,737
♪All I want now♪

426
00:16:47,737 --> 00:16:49,837
♪Is to pray for
my lady's peace and safety♪

427
00:16:49,837 --> 00:16:53,097
♪Year after year♪
